title.narrative: OUTPUT 3.1 QUALITY NEWBORN CARE

description.narrative: Output 1 (Quality newborn care): Government and partners at national and subnational levels have strengthened capacity to plan, implement, monitor and deliver equitable quality essential newborn services, which contributes to Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Newborns, children and adolescents in Indonesia's decentralized context live in healthy environments and have equitable access to high quality primary health care, especially in most marginalized, underserved regions.

title.narrative: Output 1 (Quality newborn care): Government and partners at national and subnational levels have strengthened capacity to plan,implement, monitor and deliver equitable quality essential newborn services

description.narrative: To address stagnant maternal and newborn mortality, improving quality of care remains a critical area of focus for UNICEF. This includes supporting the adoption of quality improvement approaches at health facility levels, maternal and perinatal death audits, and specific assistance to improve care of vulnerable infants, including infants with lowbirthweight, possible serious bacterial infection and those bornto HIV-positive mothers. Furthermore, as part of the overall COVID-19 response, support to continuity of essential health services remains a priority focus for UNICEF. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/01/2022
